  "description": "本書下巻では、危険に対する警戒心、人間社会と宗教の関係性と重要度の変化、消えつつある言語の多様性と、社会における多言語の使用、非感染性疾患と西洋的な生活様式といった人間社会の諸問題を取り上げる。伝統的社会に強く惹かれ、研究者としての人生の大半をニューギニアなどの伝統的社会に捧げてきたジャレド・ダイアモンドが、現代西洋社会に住む私たちが学ぶべき人類の叡知を紹介する。, Japanese edition of The World Until Yesterday: What Can We Learn from Traditional Societies? by Jared Diamond. A fascinating look at primitive societies and how they live compared to new modern industrial society. Besides not having the types of health problems seen in advanced society, their solutions to universal human problems such as child rearing, elder care, dispute resolution, risk, and physical fitness have much to teach us. A great book to spark thought and debate. vol. 2 of 2. In Japanese. Annotation copyright Tsai Fong Books, Inc. Distributed by Tsai Fong Books, Inc.",
